<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-31T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-31T19:00:00-05:00" n="781" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d781">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3584</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LM1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Langhorne</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-31T19:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>462. Your 798, March 23, 4 p.m. It is assumed by this Government that the
                            position of the Dutch Government has no reference to the armed vessels
                            of neutral countries which may enter Dutch ports as ships of commerce.
                            This Government would be pleased to have this view confirmed by the
                            Government of the Netherlands.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>